race.comment: HEMAN (8) did a great job to score by a long neck over this track and trip when resuming from a spell and will have derived benefit from that hit-out. Has only missed a top-two spot once in five starts around this circuit and gets some weight off from the inside marble. Plenty to like about his prospects. ANEMACORE (5) resumes here but has a win and two seconds from three first-up attempts and a strong showing while fresh would not surprise. The well-related WARBY (1) (half to G1 winner Captivant) grows a leg for hoop Maloney who has four wins and three placings from just eight steers. Watch for sharp improvement. THE LITTLE PUMPER (6) will be at peak fitness now fourth run back and can trouble the judge from the low draw. SENESCHAL (10) is usually thereabouts and may earn another cheque.
